If the commissioner finds that any person has violated any provision of KRS 304.3-500 to 304.3-570 or KRS 304.9-440, the commissioner may order:
For each separate violation, a civil penalty in the amounts set forth in KRS 304.99-020;
Conditions upon, or revocation, or suspension of a license;
The controlling agent to reimburse the insurer, the rehabilitator, or the liquidator of the insurer for any losses incurred by the insurer caused by a violation of KRS 304.3-500 to 304.3-570 or KRS 304.9-440 committed by the controlling agent; or
Any combination of paragraphs (a), (b), or (c) of this subsection.
